1
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:12,933
<i>I've already called that contact
at the job fair.</i>

2
00:00:13,067 --> 00:00:14,167
<i> He'll take care of you.</i>

3
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:16,133
<i> Just take care of Tere.</i>

4
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:18,600
<i>Oh, yes, Sir!
I won't neglect her, Sir!</i>

5
00:00:18,733 --> 00:00:19,467
<i> What?</i>

6
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,533
<i> Get down there!</i>

7
00:00:20,667 --> 00:00:21,667
<i> You think I'm scared?</i>

8
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:23,167
<i> You're arrogant!</i>

9
00:00:29,367 --> 00:00:30,567
<i> Anyone else?</i>

10
00:00:32,133 --> 00:00:32,733
<i> Hi, Miss!</i>

11
00:00:32,867 --> 00:00:34,400
<i>Can I take some pictures of you?</i>

12
00:00:34,567 --> 00:00:35,867
<i>- Tere, right?
- Yes. Tere.</i>

13
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,000
<i> Have a drink first.</i>

14
00:00:37,533 --> 00:00:39,533
<i> I'm just a little dizzy.</i>

15
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:42,333
<i> Come on, let's go there.</i>

16
00:00:42,467 --> 00:00:43,533
<i> Seriously...</i>

17
00:00:43,667 --> 00:00:46,967
<i>If I were with Sir Tonyo
every day, I'd fall for him.</i>

18
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:48,133
<i>Will you fall for him right
away?</i>

19
00:00:48,267 --> 00:00:49,433
<i>Where are you taking my friend?</i>

20
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:51,533
<i>Bring him along!
He might make noise!</i>

21
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,733
<i> Ma'am Bobby, Sir Tonyo,</i>

22
00:00:54,867 --> 00:00:58,000
<i>let's celebrate that we made it
here alive.</i>

23
00:00:58,133 --> 00:00:59,600
<i>That's not allowed with us, Sir.</i>

24
00:00:59,733 --> 00:01:02,200
<i> All right, stop me.</i>

25
00:01:02,700 --> 00:01:03,867
<i> I said give me that.</i>

26
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:08,333
Well then, it's yours.

27
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:14,567
Let's have a drink, Sir.

28
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:16,633
I'll just remind you, Sir.

29
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,700
We're at work.

30
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:24,767
Oh my, your wife won't like
that.

31
00:01:28,033 --> 00:01:29,300
You're married, Sir?

32
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:35,633
Yes, but Sir Tonyo's wife
is gone.

33
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:41,167
Okay, Ma'am.
I'll use the CR first.

34
00:02:07,433 --> 00:02:08,900
<i> Raise your hands!</i>

35
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:19,767
Why are you so angry?

36
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:21,033
Nothing happened to us.

37
00:02:21,167 --> 00:02:23,967
We're still alive and we're not
the target.

38
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:27,233
But still, you put our daughter
in a very traumatic setting.

39
00:02:27,367 --> 00:02:29,533
Faye hasn't even recovered
from the kidnapping,

40
00:02:29,667 --> 00:02:30,233
and now this!

41
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:34,600
We need to go out in public
as a family!

42
00:02:35,033 --> 00:02:37,100
Dad, please.

43
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,867
I agree with Mom.

44
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,567
Can you just stay here
for the next few days?

45
00:02:41,700 --> 00:02:44,667
I'll cancel your attendance
at the debate.

46
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:45,300
No.

47
00:02:45,700 --> 00:02:46,767
What will people say?

48
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,033
That I'm a coward?

49
00:02:48,167 --> 00:02:49,267
And I have nothing to say

50
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,767
about the issues Victor
is throwing at me!

51
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:54,433
Dad, it's for your own safety.

52
00:02:54,567 --> 00:02:55,867
Look at this.

53
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:58,800
Just a few hours after
the shootout,

54
00:02:59,133 --> 00:03:00,867
riders were being shot
at on the highway.

55
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:01,667
What?

56
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,067
It's not safe out there.

57
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:05,067
As long as you can't stop me!

58
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:07,767
Tomorrow, I'll face Victor

59
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:11,000
so people will know
that his brain is empty!

60
00:03:15,067 --> 00:03:16,167
Joaquin?

61
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:26,900
Yes, there you go.
One, two, three...

62
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:29,033
- Congratulations.
- Okay.

63
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:31,400
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you very much.

64
00:03:31,533 --> 00:03:35,433
I'm sorry I didn't give the
check to you right away because,

65
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,400
there was a sudden commotion
earlier.

66
00:03:37,533 --> 00:03:39,567
There's no problem, Amo.

67
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:40,600
Thank you.

68
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:45,133
Major, is there any news
about the gunman?

69
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:48,300
Amo, we still don't have any
leads.

70
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:55,633
So, who is the target
of this shooter?

71
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:58,267
Well, I'm worried about
the debate tomorrow.

72
00:03:59,833 --> 00:04:02,667
We're still not sure, Amo.

73
00:04:02,967 --> 00:04:04,367
But don't worry.

74
00:04:04,667 --> 00:04:07,900
We're on alert for the debate
tomorrow.

75
00:04:12,733 --> 00:04:15,033
Lieutenant Conde, is he here?

76
00:04:15,167 --> 00:04:17,100
I would like to hand him
a check.

77
00:04:18,267 --> 00:04:19,533
They're not there, Amo.

78
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:21,267
They're on duty.

79
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:22,667
Is that so?

80
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,400
Okay, just hand it to them.

81
00:04:25,533 --> 00:04:26,333
Okay, Amo.

82
00:04:28,133 --> 00:04:29,200
Thank you.

83
00:04:29,333 --> 00:04:31,800
- Thank you very much.
- Congratulations.

84
00:04:31,933 --> 00:04:32,600
Sir.

85
00:04:35,667 --> 00:04:37,833
Sir, I'm sorry.

86
00:04:37,967 --> 00:04:39,667
Next time, Enriquez,

87
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:44,467
don't use my personal life
to correct me.

88
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:48,767
Sorry, Sir, but my point is,
we know drinking is wrong.

89
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:52,367
Please, Enriquez,
leave me alone?

90
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,567
I'm trying to work my way
with Selena.

91
00:04:58,267 --> 00:05:00,667
So you're working your way
with Selena?

92
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,033
So that explains it.

93
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:05,033
Okay, I won't interfere
with you anymore.

94
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,867
What's your problem, Enriquez?

95
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,300
You've been like that
for a while.

96
00:05:10,433 --> 00:05:13,167
Sir, I'm just doing my job here.

97
00:05:13,300 --> 00:05:14,800
Are you guys fighting?

98
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:18,400
Oh my, that's enough.

99
00:05:18,533 --> 00:05:21,367
Sonny and I used to be
like that.

100
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:26,067
We're pretending that we were
pissed off with each other,

101
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:28,767
but the truth is,
we like each other.

102
00:05:31,533 --> 00:05:33,000
Us?

103
00:05:33,133 --> 00:05:34,500
That's impossible!

104
00:05:37,367 --> 00:05:38,367
Come on, Selena.

105
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,200
Let's just drink inside.

106
00:05:49,733 --> 00:05:51,133
His style is really something
else.

107
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:53,067
So he's interested in her.

108
00:05:54,667 --> 00:05:56,300
I thought I offended him.

109
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:00,033
Ma'am Bobby,

110
00:06:00,167 --> 00:06:04,367
is it really okay for you
if I drink with Sir Tonyo?

111
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,200
No, that's not allowed,

112
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,300
but he wants to,
so it's up to him.

113
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,800
Really?

114
00:06:11,933 --> 00:06:13,100
Thank you.

115
00:06:16,633 --> 00:06:19,000
She, too, is so mischievous.

116
00:06:19,133 --> 00:06:21,633
Her boyfriend just died.

117
00:06:27,033 --> 00:06:28,400
Tie them up tightly.

118
00:06:34,933 --> 00:06:35,800
Chris!

119
00:06:35,933 --> 00:06:36,633
Boss.

120
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,133
Is that okay, Boss?

121
00:06:43,933 --> 00:06:45,033
Very good.

122
00:06:45,167 --> 00:06:47,700
Our buyers in Europe
are waiting for it.

123
00:06:53,467 --> 00:06:54,367
What's this?

124
00:06:55,733 --> 00:06:58,000
Why did you bring a pest here?

125
00:07:00,833 --> 00:07:05,133
Didn't I make it clear that you
should only take women?

126
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:08,167
Does this look like a woman?

127
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:10,767
Well, boss,
that one is so noisy.

128
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:17,100
This one is just a burden here.

129
00:07:18,267 --> 00:07:19,633
Dispose him later, okay?

130
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:22,300
Come with me.

131
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,033
<i> Hello, Paloma?</i>

132
00:07:58,167 --> 00:07:59,167
Hello, Chief?

133
00:07:59,300 --> 00:08:00,600
I need backup.

134
00:08:00,733 --> 00:08:02,400
I followed a kidnapper.

135
00:08:02,533 --> 00:08:04,833
They kidnapped someone
at the Calabari Job Fair,

136
00:08:04,967 --> 00:08:06,567
and it looks like I'm already
in their hideout.

137
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,033
I'll send you the location.

138
00:08:09,167 --> 00:08:10,067
Okay, Chief.

139
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:14,667
Tere...

140
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,100
Hello, Bok? Sorry.

141
00:09:26,233 --> 00:09:27,167
I have an emergency.

142
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:29,467
Bok, this is an emergency
for you, too.

143
00:09:29,633 --> 00:09:31,700
My man followed a kidnapper.

144
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:34,667
They victimized someone there
at the Calabari Job Fair.

145
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:35,433
What?

146
00:09:35,567 --> 00:09:36,733
Where's your guy?

147
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:00,433
Tere...

148
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:02,333
Tere...

149
00:10:09,167 --> 00:10:09,433
Tere...

150
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,267
Tere...

151
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:14,433
Tere...

152
00:10:16,067 --> 00:10:17,900
Hey! Wake up!

153
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:23,800
Tere...

154
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:27,200
Tere...

155
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:28,967
Caloy?

156
00:10:31,300 --> 00:10:32,533
Where are we?

157
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:34,533
Where are we?

158
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:36,167
What are we doing here?

159
00:10:37,100 --> 00:10:37,933
Tere...

160
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:41,633
We've been kidnapped.

161
00:10:41,767 --> 00:10:42,300
What?

162
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:43,400
We've been kidnapped.

163
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:50,233
I hope your uncle will read
my message.

164
00:10:50,367 --> 00:10:51,500
Did you text Uncle?

165
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:52,567
Yes, I texted him.

166
00:10:52,700 --> 00:10:53,700
Wait, wait.

167
00:10:53,833 --> 00:10:54,700
Come on.

168
00:10:57,033 --> 00:10:59,233
Hey, wake up.

169
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:00,300
Hey...

170
00:11:01,733 --> 00:11:03,067
Get rid of mine.

171
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:05,133
Wait, sorry.

172
00:11:29,300 --> 00:11:29,967
Who are you?

173
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:31,933
Raise your hand!

174
00:11:34,900 --> 00:11:36,400
Get the girls ready.

175
00:11:36,533 --> 00:11:38,567
Tomorrow,
we'll send them on their way.

176
00:11:48,667 --> 00:11:49,533
That's a gun.

177
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:50,933
- That's a gun!
- Calm down, calm down.

178
00:11:51,067 --> 00:11:51,667
Calm down, calm down, calm down.

179
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:52,367
What's that?

180
00:11:53,767 --> 00:11:54,800
Boss, boss!

181
00:11:54,933 --> 00:11:56,233
There's an intruder!

182
00:11:56,367 --> 00:11:58,033
Go check that out!

183
00:11:58,167 --> 00:11:58,900
Let's go.

184
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:13,600
Faster!

185
00:12:15,767 --> 00:12:17,567
Just a moment. Don't...

186
00:12:17,700 --> 00:12:21,400
- Let's go, Sir Tonyo. Cheers.
- Cheers.

187
00:12:21,533 --> 00:12:22,567
All right, cheers.

188
00:12:32,567 --> 00:12:34,967
You know, Sir Tonyo,

189
00:12:36,100 --> 00:12:38,700
you're cute when you smile.

190
00:12:38,833 --> 00:12:40,533
You really look like someone.

191
00:12:41,633 --> 00:12:42,600
Who?

192
00:12:42,733 --> 00:12:44,700
Our future child.

193
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:50,600
Do you want that? Just kidding,
I'm kidding.

194
00:12:50,767 --> 00:12:54,067
I'm sorry. I'm really like this
when I'm drunk.

195
00:12:55,767 --> 00:12:56,600
One more.

196
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:59,333
But seriously,

197
00:12:59,467 --> 00:13:03,800
didn't you and Sonny ever talk
about getting married

198
00:13:03,933 --> 00:13:06,533
or having kids?

199
00:13:07,567 --> 00:13:09,467
Of course, we talked about it.

200
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:13,100
But the problem is that
Sonny doesn't like it

201
00:13:13,233 --> 00:13:17,467
because his job is hard.

202
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:20,367
And his boss is demanding,

203
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:22,433
it's like the boss
is strangling his neck.

204
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:26,867
Wait, strangling his neck?

205
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,700
What do you mean by strangling
his neck?

206
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:35,500
Well, he can't say no,
and his boss keeps calling,

207
00:13:35,633 --> 00:13:39,833
but he's getting paid a lot.

208
00:13:39,967 --> 00:13:42,267
That's why he bought me
a necklace

209
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:44,633
with an emerald pendant.

210
00:14:24,933 --> 00:14:25,633
Hurry!

211
00:14:52,367 --> 00:14:53,367
Are you Paloma?

212
00:14:53,633 --> 00:14:54,267
Yes, Sir.

213
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:55,933
Go there.

214
00:14:56,067 --> 00:14:56,867
Over there.

215
00:15:32,467 --> 00:15:33,300
Dizon!

216
00:15:48,633 --> 00:15:50,100
Here.

217
00:15:50,233 --> 00:15:51,500
Look, look.

218
00:15:57,567 --> 00:15:59,600
It's beautiful, isn't it?

219
00:15:59,733 --> 00:16:07,167
You know I told Sonny,
I'll never lose this,

220
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:10,933
sell it, pawn it.

221
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,333
It's beautiful.

222
00:16:12,467 --> 00:16:13,633
It looks good on me.

223
00:16:14,667 --> 00:16:16,667
Can you put it on me?

224
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:19,433
I'm already dizzy.

225
00:16:19,567 --> 00:16:20,433
What's this?

226
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:24,133
There.

227
00:16:28,100 --> 00:16:31,767
By the way, Sonny's Boss,

228
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:36,467
did he mention to you who
it was?

229
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:39,833
Yes.

230
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:40,967
Who?

231
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:44,700
Did he tell you who...

232
00:16:45,033 --> 00:16:45,733
who?

233
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:49,333
Yes.

234
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:50,100
Who?

235
00:16:53,567 --> 00:16:55,167
I really don't remember.

236
00:17:19,367 --> 00:17:20,900
Give it to me. Let me.

237
00:17:21,033 --> 00:17:22,467
Okay, wait, wait.

238
00:17:23,733 --> 00:17:25,767
Take it easy, take it easy.

239
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:27,933
Mister...

240
00:17:28,067 --> 00:17:29,267
Please, please!

241
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:32,900
- Have mercy.
- I'm a policeman.

242
00:17:33,033 --> 00:17:37,833
Sir, they're here!

243
00:17:41,567 --> 00:17:44,467
- Tere.
- Uncle...

244
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,600
Dizon, Robles, get them out.

245
00:17:50,967 --> 00:17:52,867
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

246
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:53,700
You weren't hurt?

247
00:17:55,633 --> 00:17:56,700
Sir...

248
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:57,500
Caloy.

249
00:17:57,633 --> 00:17:58,533
I'm sorry.

250
00:17:58,667 --> 00:18:01,400
I didn't do anything
to save Tere.

251
00:18:01,533 --> 00:18:02,767
Caloy, thank you.

252
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:04,333
You didn't abandon Tere.

253
00:18:04,467 --> 00:18:05,433
You did a good job.

254
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:06,433
Thank you very much.

255
00:18:06,567 --> 00:18:08,367
Thank you, Sir.

256
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:09,400
Tere.

257
00:18:09,533 --> 00:18:12,200
Lieutenant Paloma,
thank you very much.

258
00:18:13,367 --> 00:18:15,033
It's good that you followed
them.

259
00:18:15,167 --> 00:18:16,633
It's nothing, Sir.

260
00:18:16,767 --> 00:18:18,933
Actually, I'm following
a syndicate lead.

261
00:18:19,067 --> 00:18:21,300
It has to do with human
trafficking.

262
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:23,833
And I have a feeling,
they did this.

263
00:18:23,967 --> 00:18:27,500
You know, there are rampant
criminals here in Calabari.

264
00:18:27,633 --> 00:18:33,033
If I find out who's behind this,
I won't respect them.

265
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:37,567
Lieutenant, if you need my help,
just call me.

266
00:18:38,767 --> 00:18:39,467
Thank you very much.

267
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:40,200
Okay, Sir.

268
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:41,133
Let's go.

269
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:44,933
- Caloy.
- Okay.

270
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:50,467
This one is hard-headed,
and he is so arrogant.

271
00:18:51,567 --> 00:18:52,633
Okay.

272
00:18:52,767 --> 00:18:54,267
I'll just wait for your text.

273
00:19:01,167 --> 00:19:03,733
I just spoke with my contact
in the police.

274
00:19:03,867 --> 00:19:06,233
He doesn't know the exact
address of the safehouse

275
00:19:06,367 --> 00:19:08,800
because only the two
escort police officers

276
00:19:08,933 --> 00:19:10,567
know the exact address.

277
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:11,967
So what?

278
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:13,433
We failed?

279
00:19:13,567 --> 00:19:16,633
My contact will find out
which police safehouses

280
00:19:16,767 --> 00:19:17,800
are in the area.

281
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:21,167
He told me that there are
around 3 to 5 safehouses,

282
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:22,767
so we will check one by one.

283
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:29,467
What's with Grandmother?

284
00:19:30,967 --> 00:19:33,800
Why did she send me
this kind of clothes?

285
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:37,300
Oh my.

286
00:19:40,133 --> 00:19:43,467
Why does his boss
have so much money?

287
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,033
Where does he get it from?

288
00:19:46,167 --> 00:19:48,500
Where else, from the local
treasury?

289
00:19:48,633 --> 00:19:50,233
Oh, cheers!

290
00:19:50,933 --> 00:19:51,967
Cheers!

291
00:19:53,533 --> 00:19:55,567
They're laughing.

292
00:19:58,100 --> 00:19:59,533
They must be drunk.

293
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:03,300
What are these two doing?

294
00:20:03,467 --> 00:20:04,733
Local treasury.

295
00:20:05,767 --> 00:20:06,900
What town is this?

296
00:20:08,667 --> 00:20:09,800
I don't know.

297
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:14,733
All I know is that he gives
Sonny a lot of money.

298
00:20:14,867 --> 00:20:18,733
That's why I got this beautiful
necklace.

299
00:20:18,867 --> 00:20:23,533
But this, this is just our
secret.

300
00:20:23,667 --> 00:20:25,567
I'll tell this only to you.

301
00:20:35,867 --> 00:20:39,400
Sonny is in my heart.

302
00:20:40,467 --> 00:20:41,967
Do you want to see it?

303
00:20:42,100 --> 00:20:43,633
I'll show you something.

304
00:20:45,167 --> 00:20:46,933
This, look at it.

305
00:20:47,067 --> 00:20:48,233
There.

306
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,200
This is Sonny,

307
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:54,767
just a little one.

308
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,100
No, it's big.

309
00:20:56,233 --> 00:20:58,500
I mean, your heart is big.

310
00:20:58,633 --> 00:21:01,400
Of course, Sonny has that too.

311
00:21:01,533 --> 00:21:03,033
Do you want it too?

312
00:21:07,433 --> 00:21:08,267
Who's that?

313
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:12,133
Maybe it's Sonny,

314
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:15,067
haunting you.

315
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:16,533
I guess he misses you.

316
00:21:18,867 --> 00:21:21,633
You know,
I'm not afraid of ghosts.

317
00:21:21,767 --> 00:21:27,733
I'm afraid of feelings
that are not explored.

318
00:21:36,567 --> 00:21:38,000
Just kidding!

319
00:21:40,067 --> 00:21:41,067
I'm sorry.

320
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:43,100
I'm really like this
when I'm drunk.

321
00:21:43,267 --> 00:21:45,667
Sonny gets mad at me
when I'm like this.

322
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:49,333
Come on, one more shot.

323
00:22:04,867 --> 00:22:07,067
Oh my God, Bobby.

324
00:22:08,967 --> 00:22:10,867
Is your name Marites?

325
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:15,400
If they want to flirt,

326
00:22:16,833 --> 00:22:19,767
then let them flirt.

327
00:22:19,900 --> 00:22:21,833
They're old enough.

328
00:22:21,967 --> 00:22:23,867
You should ignore them.

329
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:26,867
You shouldn't be messing
with those two.

330
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:30,367
Maybe later Sir Tonyo will say
something to you.

331
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:33,333
Hey, Enriquez!

332
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:35,167
Sir?

333
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:37,633
Why are you watching over Selena
and me?

334
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:40,400
Oh, no, Sir.

335
00:22:40,533 --> 00:22:42,233
Just so you know,

336
00:22:44,367 --> 00:22:47,333
nothing happened between us.

337
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:50,933
I don't like her anyway.

338
00:22:51,067 --> 00:22:53,367
Do you know what I want?

339
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:55,467
For you to get jealous!

340
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:56,600
Sir?

341
00:22:57,900 --> 00:22:59,833
Me, get jealous?

342
00:22:59,967 --> 00:23:00,500
Why, Sir?

343
00:23:00,633 --> 00:23:01,367
Yes.

344
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:06,700
So I can know if you have
feelings for me.

345
00:23:06,833 --> 00:23:08,667
Because, as for me,

346
00:23:10,067 --> 00:23:17,767
I'm feel a lot even before
so if you love me, admit it.

347
00:23:20,333 --> 00:23:22,233
Because I...

348
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,467
I love you.

349
00:23:46,233 --> 00:23:48,367
- El Hepe!
- El Hepe!

350
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:49,467
Hey, hey, what's that?

351
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:50,600
Hey!

352
00:23:50,733 --> 00:23:54,967
I have no problem
with Sir Tonyo.

353
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:59,300
And when I saw Ma'am Bobby
last night,

354
00:23:59,467 --> 00:24:02,767
she seemed very demure
and could not break a plate.

355
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:06,000
I think I know
who their boss is.

356
00:24:06,133 --> 00:24:09,233
I think he is the one who
is trying to kill me.

357
00:24:09,367 --> 00:24:10,133
Who?

358
00:24:10,267 --> 00:24:11,067
I'm disappointed.

359
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,233
She's still alive.

360
00:24:12,367 --> 00:24:14,500
She will die soon.

361
00:24:14,633 --> 00:24:17,300
Amo is your father, right, Sir?
